  "translations": {
    "en": "Then know, O Muhammad ibn Abu Bakr! I have appointed you to govern the greatest of my troops in my mind: the people of Egypt. When I have given you that appointment, you deserve most to be cautious about yourself and watchful over your faith. Try your best not to displease your Lord for the sake of people's pleasure, for in Allah's pleasure there is a substitute for everything else, but in anything else there is no substitute for Him. Be severe to the oppressors, censure them. Be lenient to the righteous, bring them closer, and appoint them in your inner circle of brotherhood.",
    "ur": "Then know, O Muhammad ibn Abu Bakr! I have appointed you to govern the greatest of my troops in my mind: the people of Egypt. When I have given you that appointment, you deserve most to be cautious about yourself and watchful over your faith. Try your best not to displease your Lord for the sake of people's pleasure, for in Allah's pleasure there is a substitute for everything else, but in anything else there is no substitute for Him. Be severe to the oppressors, censure them. Be lenient to the righteous, bring them closer, and appoint them in your inner circle of brotherhood.",
    "tr": "Then know, O Muhammad ibn Abu Bakr! I have appointed you to govern the greatest of my troops in my mind: the people of Egypt. When I have given you that appointment, you deserve most to be cautious about yourself and watchful over your faith. Try your best not to displease your Lord for the sake of people's pleasure, for in Allah's pleasure there is a substitute for everything else, but in anything else there is no substitute for Him. Be severe to the oppressors, censure them. Be lenient to the righteous, bring them closer, and appoint them in your inner circle of brotherhood.",
